<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,334,722,748]" box="[189,334,722,748]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,722,748]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,722,748]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1219,769,796]" box="[189,1219,769,796]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
MEASUREMENTS. Body length: male 6.2–7.0 mm (N = 56), female 
<quantity box="[962,1104,769,795]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.45" metricValueMax="7.7" metricValueMin="7.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="7.45" valueMax="7.7" valueMin="7.2">7.2–7.7 mm</quantity>
(N = 19).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[187,1400,827,1064]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
COLORATION. General color yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[748,881,827,853]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3A–B</figureCitation>
). Eyes blackish brown, ocelli faint yellow, semi-translucent.Antenna, vertex, face and rostrum generally blackish brown. Pronotum and mesonotum blackish brown. Forewing semi-translucent, costal vein with a small dark brown spot; posterior to stigma, in centre of forewing and posterior to clavus with an irregular puce spot, respectively; basal and middle part of forewing with two inner oblique yellow stripes; apical half of forewing with brown patches. Stigma light brown. Veins yellowish brown. Tubercles brown. Hind tibiae yellowish brown. Ventral abdomen blackish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1096,1298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
HEAD AND THORAX. Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[520,647,1096,1122]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3A, C</figureCitation>
) 1.1× as long as wide; lateral carinae strongly elevated, median carina absent. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[449,543,1131,1157]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
) 3.1× as long as wide. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[969,1100,1131,1157]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3A, C</figureCitation>
) 1.7× as long as vertex; posterior margin forming an obtuse angle. Mesonotum 1.1× as long as pronotum and vertex combined. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[320,448,1201,1228]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3B, E</figureCitation>
) 2.5 × as long as wide, with thirteen apical cells and seven subapical cells; RP with 4 branches; MP with 5 branches (MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[687,703,1255,1269]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">11</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[761,778,1255,1269]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">12</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[836,845,1255,1269]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">2</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[902,911,1255,1269]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">3</subScript>
, and MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1018,1027,1255,1269]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">4</subScript>
); fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1152,1161,1255,1269]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">1</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1226,1235,1255,1269]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">2</subScript>
basad of fork MP
</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[231,240,1291,1305]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">3</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1096,1298]" box="[244,306,1272,1298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">+MP</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[306,315,1291,1305]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">4</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1096,1298]" box="[315,1260,1272,1298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">. Metatibiotarsal formula 7/8, second segment of hind tarsus with three platellae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[187,1401,1330,1848]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
MALE GENITALIA. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[505,628,1330,1356]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3F–G</figureCitation>
) in ventral view symmetrical; in lateral view, lateral lobes arcuate and extended caudally. Medioventral process rectangular (much wider than long). Anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[198,316,1400,1426]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3F, H</figureCitation>
) flat tubular, dOrsal margin almOst straight, ventral margin straight (parallel tO dOrsal margin), bending 90 degrees into apical lobe; 1.6× as long as wide in dorsal view; anal style strap-shaped, not extending beyond anal segment. Gonostyli (
<figureCitation box="[724,846,1470,1497]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3G, I</figureCitation>
) symmetrical in ventral view; in inner lateral view, base of dorsal margin concave, ventral margin with a small process, middle part of apical margin of gonostyli deeply emarginate, forming two processes: a large process around ventral margin, apical margin rounded; another small, around dorsal margin, apical margin pointed. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1266,1392,1576,1602]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[235,1340,266,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-104@8.[232,1356,257,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862175/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3J–M</figureCitation>
) with six processes. Ventral margin of periandrium with a sub-triangular process; apical left side of process with a short, small spinose process, directed ventrad; right side of process expanded, forming a laminal prOcess, curved upward, directed cephalad; basal ⅓ Of right side Of periandrium with a hOrn-like spinose process, directed dorsocaudad; dorsal margin with a straight medium-length spinose process, directed right-dorsocephalad. Endosoma curved towards left, apical margin gradually narrowed, forming a spinOse prOcess, margin with small teeth; basal ⅓ Of right side with a laminal prOcess, margin with small teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[188,1400,1880,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
FEMALE GENITALIA. Tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[554,715,1880,1906]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[188,231,1400,1426]" captionTargetBox="[196,1392,276,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-149@9.[191,1400,265,1389]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. I. Posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862177/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 4A–B, D</figureCitation>
) moderately sclerotized, with a large, nearly quadrate wax plate. Anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[442,534,1915,1942]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[188,231,1400,1426]" captionTargetBox="[196,1392,276,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-149@9.[191,1400,265,1389]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. I. Posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862177/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) rectangular, 1.6× as long as wide in dorsal view, anal style linguiform. Gonapophysis VIII (
<figureCitation box="[437,528,1951,1977]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[188,231,1400,1426]" captionTargetBox="[196,1392,276,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-149@9.[191,1400,265,1389]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. I. Posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862177/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
) elongate and slightly curved upwards. Gonapophysis IX (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1329,1951,1977]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[188,231,1400,1426]" captionTargetBox="[196,1392,276,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-149@9.[191,1400,265,1389]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Andes bifidus Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. I. Posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862177/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
) with one middle tooth, distance ratio between middle tooth to apex and length of denticulate portion 2.4.
</paragraph>
